cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

The paper deals with the problem of semi-supervised learning with convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The techniques used in the paper, such as randomized data augmentation, dropout, and random max-pooling, are also commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also proposes an unsupervised loss function, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
